==Russian==

===Letter===
{{infl|ru|letter|lower case||upper case|Б}}

# The second letter of the Russian [[Cyrillic]] alphabet. Its name is '''бэ''' {{IPAchar|(bɛ)}} and it has the sound of English '''b'''. It is preceded by [[а|А]] and followed by [[в|В]].

===Particle===
'''б''', '''[[бы]]''' (b, by) ''(conditional particle)''

# б is the short form of [[бы]], a verbal particle used to render [[conditional]] and [[subjunctive]] patterns:
#:: [[я|Я]] [[говорить|говорил]] — ''I spoke''
#: [[я|Я]] б [[говорить|говорил]] — ''I would (should) have spoken; I would speak; I might speak''
#: [[я|Я]] [[говорить|говорил]] [[бы]] — ''I would (should) have spoken; I would speak; I might speak''

'''N.B.''' — [[бы]] is the [[third-person singular]] [[aorist]] of [[быть]] ''(to be)'', an otherwise obsolete Russian tense.

